doc.after: About one quarter of the airline's carrying capacity vanished as a result of the crash.[32] Following the crash of OE-LAV, the airline had no flights to Sydney, on 1, 6, and 7 June. Flights resumed with another 767 on 13 June.[33] Niki Lauda said that the crash in 1991 and the period after was the worst time in his life.[19]
